From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: LibreStation Timestamp Build <root@localhost>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 15:40:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] ip-gadget: fix TX last packet payload length

The IP gadget TX streamer builds each UDP datagram from two iovecs:
one for the data_ip_hdr_t header and one for payload. The payload iovec
must contain only payload bytes. The last packet path accidentally added
the header size again, sending extra bytes at the end of non-aligned TX
buffers.
---
 PlutoSDR_TXStreamerIPGadget.cpp | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/PlutoSDR_TXStreamerIPGadget.cpp b/PlutoSDR_TXStreamerIPGadget.cpp
--- a/PlutoSDR_TXStreamerIPGadget.cpp
+++ b/PlutoSDR_TXStreamerIPGadget.cpp
@@ -391,7 +391,9 @@ void tx_streamer_ip_gadget::thread_func(uint32_t curr_enabled_channels, uint32_t
 		{
 			/* Last packet, work out how many bytes of the payload it will contain */
 			size_t iio_buffer_size = buffer_size_samples * sample_size_bytes;
-			arr_iovs[(2 * i) + 1].iov_len = sizeof(data_ip_hdr_t) + (iio_buffer_size % udp_payload_size);
+			size_t last_payload_size = iio_buffer_size % udp_payload_size;
+			if (last_payload_size == 0) last_payload_size = udp_payload_size;
+			arr_iovs[(2 * i) + 1].iov_len = last_payload_size;
 		}
 
 		/* Prepare packet headers, just need to fill in the sequence number at transmission time */
